description.0: The X-Men are lost in space!
description.10: Luke's'new mentor,'Jedi Master'C'Baoth, is teaching him new ways to use the Force, ways that seem inappropriate. But ways that may become necessary in light of the fact that'Grand Admiral'Thrawn'has taken command of the remnants of the'Imperial fleet.
description.11: Before the Empire held sway over the galaxy... before the Rebel forces rose up to create the New Republic... there was the time of the Old Republic. The story of how that grand oligarchy fell from power begins here, in an episode titled "First Encounter".
description.12: Gorga'may want to call off the hit, the target being his father-in-law and Gorga's wife being suddenly pregnant and all, but'Boba Fett'was promised a contract, and he doesn't do last-minute cancellations. It's a knockdown, drag-out roustabout in'Boba Fett: Murder Most Foul!
description.22: Wedge Antilles is the ace pilot of the Rebel Alliance, and his Rogue Squadron is the outfit of choice for every X-wing flyer. But just as the New Republic has its star space jockeys, so does the Empire. And Baron Fel and the Imperial 181st Fighter Division are hungry to see what Rogue Squadron is made of. Don't miss the comics premier of Baron Fel, the Empire's greatest fighter ace!
description.23: Dane Whitman, A.K.A. the Black Knight, joins Oracle Inc. as a scientist/teammate, and leaps into action with the H4H against Nitro!
description.24: When Elektra is paid to keep the police's star witness from the clutches of a fearsome quartet known as the Four Winds, she quickly begins to wonder if the job and the witness is worth the money!
description.29: Humiliated by his defeat, Spider-Man decides to join forces with X-Man to defeat Electro who plans to blackmail the city with an electrical bomb. Will Spider-Man finally defeat Electro or get humiliated again?
description.30: Vulture guts the fake Prowler and reverts to his previous state!
description.35: Humbled by the power of the Ancient One, Stephen Strange, a former neurosurgeon, gains the mystic prowess of the Sorcerer Supreme! The all-seeing Eye of Agamotto will reveal all!
description.37: He took on the Wolverine, and now the Hulk will face off with the rest of the X-Men! But what do the mutants want with the Hulk?
description.41: With X-Men missing... Marrow goes wild! And Spider-Man makes a special appearance!
description.47: Jori Daragon is on trial for offenses against Empress Teta's government. But far from being a lawbreaker, Jori is trying to reach the Empress, to warn her of the dark plans of the Sith Empire. If she is found guilty, she will be confined to a colony planet. And then nothing will stand between the Empress and the Sith.
description.48: The original Thunderbolts assemble against Baron Zemo and Hydra's many heads!
description.54: Concluding the epic battle between the Rogue Squadron Rebels and the Sith-tainted Imperials! A member of Rogue Squadron makes the ultimate sacrifice in this concluding chapter of Requiem for a Rogue!
description.57: Stan Lee takes you, the reader, through the TRUE origins of the original X-Men!
description.60: Special flashback issue! The past and present collide for one of Marvel's most complicated couples, as Elektra reflects on the earliest days of her love affair with Matt Murdock.
description.64: In this special flashback issue we get a rare opportunity to see Peter Parker's parents in action as Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D!
description.66: Wolverine faces off against his old foe, Sabretooth! After so many grudge matches, will this finally be the end of the line for one of these savage superhumans? Guest-starring Nick Fury and Carol Danvers!
description.67: Young hero Jolt wants to join the Thunderbolts whether they want her to or not. Will she learn their dark secret?
description.72: RETURN OF SPIDER-MAN! Ben (formerly the Scarlet Spider) revamps his lifestyle with a new job, new look and of course… a new villain!
description.78: Who is the wielder of the Ebony Blade? Learn about the ancient legend of the Black Knight, as well as its current host, Dane Whitman!
description.81: Risen from the ashes of a shrouded past, the'Jedi Master'C'Baoth'teaches Luke Skywalker'new ways to use'the Force, ways which allow him to control others. Ways commonly used on the'dark side of the Force.
description.82: With'Obi-Wan Kenobi'and'Yoda'both dead,'Luke Skywalker'is in need of a new'Jedi'mentor, and he finds one in'C'Baoth. Risen from the ashes of a shrouded past, C'Baoth may prove to be just the teacher Luke needs to deliver the final blow to'Grand Admiral'Thrawn's ailing'Empire. Or he may be the Empire's last hope for turning the tide!
description.83: The Sith Empire has rallied its forces for an all-out battle for control of the galaxy. Their goal: Crush the Republic. And with so many Sith masters amongst them, the goal is not unachievable. As Naga Sadow readies his fleet to attack, one lone person threatens to undermine the entire campaign-Jori Daragon. She isn't a Jedi. She doesn't come from a military background or have a history of fighting. She's an explorer, a mapper of hyperspace who stumbled on the plans of the Sith. And she just may be the savior of the Republic.
description.90: The Bothan tourists that Wedge and crew have come to save are neither Bothans nor tourists-they're a consortium of spies assigned to follow the Emperor. Wedge is glad to know this now, but he'd have been happier to have discovered this fact before his crew were trapped on this back-water planet called Malrev IV. Now Rogue Squadron is in the middle of a firing ground, between a twisted, self-styled "Lord of the Sith" who calls Malrev 4 his home and the leader of the spies, Girov, who desires the planet, its great temple, and all its power for his own!
description.91: Finally, Elektra and the Architect collide, but all is not as it seems. The Architect passes himself off on stage as Clytemnestra! Myth and reality merge as Elektra confronts the man who seeks death at her hand.
description.92: "You are Elektra with a K and A... you used to hang with Daredevil!" Elektra returns to New York for a battle and teams up with Spider-Man to finally put an end to the True Believers. With a defeated team, Black Tarantula is not happy and journeys to New York to face Spider-man himself. GUEST STARRING: ELEKTRA!
description.99: Spider-Man and the Thunderbolts face off against the might of the Enclave!

1.text: Bobby feels the sting of betrayal by an old friend…

3.text: Galactus continues to withhold information on The Other, the being responsible for Zenn-La’s demise. Before returning to the present, Norrin gets one final moment with his beloved Shalla-Bal.

4.text: Love blossoms among the Thunderbolts but will Citizen V allow it to survive?

5.text: A fight with Doctor Doom sends Tony back in time. Why can't he remember this version of the past? Why can't he remember...Onslaught!?

6.text: This issue features the Vanisher! And a Zero Tolerance transport carries it's mutant prisoners to an unknown location…

9.text: The Daydreamer's trippy trip turns deadly when they run afoul of the Dark Hunter. Speaking of a fowl, the gang ends up on Howard's homeworld…and he's greeted as a conquering hero?!

13.text: Zero Tolerance has begun! Cable declares war!

14.text: Captain America leads a squad of elite SHIELD agents against The Sons Of The Serpent! Meanwhile, Falcon stakes out a Serpent hideout. Plus, The Serpent King's identity is revealed!

16.text: "To face the fury of the Sentinels!"

17.text: Matt Murdock visits Vincent Grazia in prison and learns his identity has been compromised! To make matters worse, Mr. Fear infiltrates Ryker’s Island and floods the prison with fear gas! A riot breaks out and it’s up to Daredevil to settle the score. Can the Man Without Fear face Fear itself?

19.text: Cloaked in mystery, the Crime Master returns…and casts his next move against Spider-Man!

20.text: When the X-Men are taken prisoner by Zero Tolerance, it's up to an injured Wolverine to save the day!

23.text: Dane Whitman, A.K.A. the Black Knight, joins Oracle Inc. as a scientist/teammate, and leaps into action with the H4H against Nitro!

24.text: When Elektra is paid to keep the police's star witness from the clutches of a fearsome quartet known as the Four Winds, she quickly begins to wonder if the job and the witness is worth the money!

25.text: Iron Man and Rebel versus The Titanium Man and The Crimson Dynamo! Meanwhile, the herald of Galactus known as Terrax speeds towards Earth!

26.text: Domino is wanted dead or alive! And Warpath ventures into the unknown!

27.text: Abandoned by The Brotherhood, Nate has no choice but to suffer alone through the poisonous side effects of the fatal CS-9 gas.

31.text: Ka-Zar is more than comfortable with his mighty jungle, but the concrete jungle presents an all-new challenge! Welcome to the Big Apple!

32.text: Eddie Brock straddles the line between life and death after being implanted with a detonating device! Dr. Yes’s Ebola plague is that much closer to being unleashed!

33.text: The Thunderbolts must take on the mind-affecting Madcap!

36.text: Excalibur faces an internal threat and a deadly betrayal!

40.text: Though Galactus has eaten, he still hungers. Next stop: Earth! Plus, The Fantastic Four and The Inhumans versus Maximus!

44.text: This issue reveals the mystery of Zenn-La’s destruction. What being is powerful enough to knock out Galactus? In 1947 New York, Alicia gives her father a dire warning of his future…

45.text: The Thunderbolts and their newest recruit, Jolt, face off against Baron Strucker and the Growing Man!

46.text: There may be no more mightier and uncanny team than the Daydreamers! What has brought together a team of Man-Thing, Franklin Richards, Howard the Duck and more?

48.text: The original Thunderbolts assemble against Baron Zemo and Hydra's many heads!

51.text: The Sons Of The Serpent have taken hostages and are preparing to terminate them! Can Captain America stop them in time? The Sons Of The Serpent know Cap won't kill, but is that still true? America has changed...has the Captain as well?

52.text: The Merc with a Mouth faces off against the clones of Marvel's most distinguished deceased.

55.text: A story from Matt Murdock's past! Battlin' Jack worries about his blind son as he moves Matt into college. But Jack doesn’t need to worry; Matt proves he can hold his own…and then some! Plus, Matt and Foggy take on pre-law!

57.text: Stan Lee takes you, the reader, through the TRUE origins of the original X-Men!

58.text: Professor Xavier and Magneto’s joint past retold! How did these onetime friends become ideological enemies?

59.text: The Heroes for Hire are born when top scientists and the Hulk are taken hostage at the United Nations in NYC! Iron Fist, White Tiger, and Hercules hit the scene!

60.text: Special flashback issue! The past and present collide for one of Marvel's most complicated couples, as Elektra reflects on the earliest days of her love affair with Matt Murdock.

61.text: A flashback into Nightcrawler's past reveals a dark chapter of love and loss during his time as a circus performer.

62.text: What really happened to Brian Banner? At last, the true story of Bruce Banner’s father!

65.text: The Fantastic Four are the prisoners of The Inhumans! And Galactus' herald makes their way towards Earth!

68.text: Flashback issue! In Asgard’s earlier age, Loki tries to steal three sacred Golden Apples for some Giants, but is stopped by Odin!

70.text: With Reed Richards' help, Iron Man digs into the mystery surround Rebel O'Reily's death. But whatever answers he may find may also lead to more questions...

71.text: X-FORCE (1991) #-1. Flashback special! A memory from John and James Proudstar’s past lives on in the present. Before he was the X-Man Thunderbird, John Proudstar was an older brother trying to do good.

73.text: Life Lessons & Lies! A special flashback issue featuring the Lord of the Hidden Jungle!

74.text: Before Eddie Brock bonded to his symbiote costume, he was a news reporter that didn’t let anything get between him and a good story. Will Eddie expose a government secret or something far worse?

75.text: Venom takes on the mad Dr. Yes who’s armed with a bio-toxin that could well topple the world!

76.text: Stan “The Man” Lee narrates a ‘hidden’ Silver Surfer story featuring Galactus and a terrifying alien abduction!

77.text: Your perfect introduction to Cable, time-tossed mutant soldier and all around renegade is in this “Flashback” issue!

80.text: The Beginning of a Beautiful Friendship!

86.text: Molten Man’s in a boardroom preparing to take part in the family business. But Mr. Fear crashes the meeting unleashing a strange gas! Matt Murdock dons his Daredevil duds and tries to get Osborn Industries back in business.

87.text: On a new job to rescue a woman from a mental institution, Deadpool must throw down with Vamp!

88.text: The enigmatic Scarecrow casts a strange web over Spider-Man. But the wall-crawler bites back!

89.text: Can Captain America find the American Spirit? And if he does, will he still want to be a hero? Follow Cap as he embarks on a journey across America to fight crime, save lives, and find meaning for his existence.

91.text: Finally, Elektra and the Architect collide, but all is not as it seems. The Architect passes himself off on stage as Clytemnestra! Myth and reality merge as Elektra confronts the man who seeks death at her hand.

94.text: Rebel O' Reilly has returned from the grave to get his revenge on Tony Stark!

95.text: A blast from the past: Dani Moonstar is back! But is she friend or foe?

97.text: Nate decides to cut ties with The Brotherhood following their theft of deadly bio-chemical gas from Department H.

99.text: Spider-Man and the Thunderbolts face off against the might of the Enclave!
